From: Sean Christopherson <seanjc@google.com>
Date: Thu, 18 Sep 2025 17:59:52 -0700
Subject: KVM: nVMX: Add consistency check for TSC_MULTIPLIER=0
Patch-mainline: v6.19-rc1
Git-commit: ae8e6ad84177456d8810a8ff3a5cf3f477fb0721
References: git-fixes

Add a missing consistency check on the TSC Multiplier being '0'.  Per the
SDM:

  If the "use TSC scaling" VM-execution control is 1, the TSC-multiplier
  must not be zero.

Fixes: d041b5ea9335 ("KVM: nVMX: Enable nested TSC scaling")
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20250919005955.1366256-7-seanjc@google.com
Signed-off-by: Sean Christopherson <seanjc@google.com>
Acked-by: Carlos López <clopez@suse.de>
---
 arch/x86/kvm/vmx/nested.c |    4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

--- a/arch/x86/kvm/vmx/nested.c
+++ b/arch/x86/kvm/vmx/nested.c
@@ -2889,6 +2889,10 @@ static int nested_check_vm_execution_con
 		}
 	}
 
+	if (nested_cpu_has2(vmcs12, SECONDARY_EXEC_TSC_SCALING) &&
+	    CC(!vmcs12->tsc_multiplier))
+		return -EINVAL;
+
 	return 0;
 }
 
